bug.short_desc: darktable-2.2.4-1 crashes with some GX80 raw files
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1274761 Typescript output from darktable run
Description of problem: darktable crashes when opening some Panasonic GX80 (.rw2) raw files in the darkroom tab, and thereafter every time on startup until the .config/darktable/ directory is wiped. Appears to be triggered by raw files shot in L.Mono mode (i.e. that have a monochrome thumbnail). Large folders of said files also cause a crash during import.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): darktable-2.2.4-1.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: Consistent on affected files.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Import small folder of GX80 raw files, including some mono images. 2. Double-click mono thumbnail.
Actual results: Aborted (core dumped) and backtrace
Expected results: Image opens in darkroom tab.
Additional info: Last pkg version I used that works OK is 2.2.1-1.
Created attachment 1274762 Last part of darktable strace, from when test file opened

Hi Ade, thank you for filling this bugreport
We need a better backtrace
# dnf debuginfo-install darktable $ gdb darktable (gdb) run and then try triggering the crash, and when it happens enter (gdb) thread apply all backtrace
Then attach it here
Also, darktable upstream developers need you to upload affected RAWs to https://raw.pixls.us/
